# Validation Checklist: {{skill_title}}

Generated {{generated_date}} by skill-generator v{{generator_version}}.
Check every box before considering this skill bundle ready for use.

## Structure

- [ ] `SKILL.md` exists at `.claude/skills/{{skill_name}}/SKILL.md` with
      valid YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description`).
- [ ] `manifest.json` exists at `.claude/manifests/{{skill_name}}/manifest.json`
      and is valid JSON.
- [ ] `role.md` exists at `.claude/roles/{{skill_name}}/role.md`.
- [ ] At least one prompt template exists under
      `.claude/prompts/{{skill_name}}/`.
- [ ] `workflow.md` exists at `.claude/workflows/{{skill_name}}/workflow.md`.
- [ ] At least one example exists under
      `.claude/skills/{{skill_name}}/examples/`.
- [ ] No file was placed outside the standard five `.claude/` subfolders
      (`skills/`, `workflows/`, `prompts/`, `roles/`, `manifests/`).

## Self-containment

- [ ] Each file can be read and understood on its own, without requiring
      the reader to have already read the others first.
- [ ] No file references an undocumented external file, script, or
      environment variable.

## Documentation

- [ ] Every generated file has a header or intro explaining its purpose.
- [ ] All `<!-- TODO -->` placeholders are either filled in or intentionally
      left for a documented next step.

## Claude Code compatibility

- [ ] `SKILL.md` frontmatter parses as valid YAML.
- [ ] `description` field states both *what* the skill does and *when* to
      trigger it.
- [ ] No frontmatter field name collides with Claude Code reserved keys.

## Architecture preservation

- [ ] No existing project file was moved, renamed, or deleted.
- [ ] No existing file's content was modified without an explicit request.
- [ ] All new files live under the project's existing `.claude/` layout.

## Overwrite safety

- [ ] If any target file already existed, it was skipped (not overwritten)
      unless the caller explicitly requested `--force`.
- [ ] The generation report clearly lists which files were `CREATED` vs
      `SKIPPED (exists)`.

## Domain readiness (only after placeholders are filled in)

- [ ] `skill_description` accurately reflects real, tested behavior — not
      aspirational behavior.
- [ ] `manifest.json` `status` field updated from `"scaffolded"` to
      `"implemented"`.
- [ ] At least one example reflects a real run, not a hypothetical one.
